      "question": "For what value of $p$ does the quadratic equation $x^2 + px + 9 = 0$ have equal roots?",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "For equal roots, the discriminant $D = b^2 - 4ac$ must be $0$.",
          "Here $a = 1, b = p, c = 9$.",
          "Set $D = p^2 - 4(1)(9) = 0$.",
          "$p^2 - 36 = 0 \\Rightarrow p^2 = 36$.",
          "Taking square root, $p = \\pm 6$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$p^2 - 4(1)(9) = 0 \\\\ p^2 = 36 \\\\ p = \\pm 6$"
      },
